Sentencas: The cathode destruction by CO2 erosion has emerged as great obstacle to solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) application.
Titulo: Antimony-doped strontium cobalt oxide as promising cathode for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell with excellent carbon dioxide tolerance

Sentencas: In this work, replacing 18.75 % cobalt with antimony in SrCoO3-delta demonstrates substantial improvements in CO2 tolerance and perfect performance recovering from 10 vol% CO2 is achieved with symmetrical and single cell test.
Titulo: Antimony-doped strontium cobalt oxide as promising cathode for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell with excellent carbon dioxide tolerance

Sentencas: Both experimental and computational results prove the weakened CO2 adsorption strength.
Titulo: Antimony-doped strontium cobalt oxide as promising cathode for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell with excellent carbon dioxide tolerance

Sentencas: In addition, outstanding oxygen transport properties is obtained with chemical oxygen surface exchange coefficient of 1.97 x 10(-3) cm s(-1) at 600 degrees C, two orders of magnitude higher than the state-of-art cathode material La0.6Sr0.4C0.2Fe0.8O3-delta.
Titulo: Antimony-doped strontium cobalt oxide as promising cathode for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell with excellent carbon dioxide tolerance

Sentencas: The single phase electrode shows brilliant oxygen reduction reaction activity with electrode resistance of 0.185 Omega cm(2) at 600 degrees C, which is attributed to the accelerated charge transfer rate and augmented adsorbed oxygen species.
Titulo: Antimony-doped strontium cobalt oxide as promising cathode for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell with excellent carbon dioxide tolerance

Sentencas: The combination of exceptional electrochemical activity and excellent CO2 tolerance demonstrates its significant advantage for practical applications as promising cathode for low-temperature SOFCs.
Titulo: Antimony-doped strontium cobalt oxide as promising cathode for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell with excellent carbon dioxide tolerance
